# cat.tsvt — a blinking cat drawn in cells. The eyes close for a beat every few
# seconds: isnow("::+[4]") holds on seconds divisible by 4, so the eye glyph
# flips; volatile() marks the cell live, so `tsv serve` (or the playground)
# redraws it on the clock. Open one with `tsv serve cat.tsvt` and watch it blink.
   /\_/\
=concat("  ( ", if(isnow("::+[4]"), "-   -", "◉   ◉"), " )") | volatile()
   )  ^  (
=if(isnow("::+[4]"), "  ( =^..^= ) ~ *blink*", "  ( =^..^= ) ~ meow") | volatile()
